    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-24T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-24T09:00:00-05:00" n="358"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/483a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MIN1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-24T10:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>882. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_OWH1">Owen</persName> [from War
                    Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 20. Your 2270, June 11, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d358fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> Delay to any Swedish steamers here was caused by the action
                    of Swedish Government in failing to name compensation ships as provided for in
                    clause 10 of the <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>We have just received the cabled advice that Sweden has ratified the permanent
                    agreement and are hastening at once to free the Swedish vessels now loaded with
                    rations here, which will count as part of the rations under the agreement just
                    now become effective by Sweden’s ratification.</p>
                <p>In view of statement of Swedish representatives here that the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Indianic</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Australic</hi> are to proceed on Line 1
                    to Australia, we will allow these vessels to proceed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
